<subSubSection lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="104" pageId="2" pageNumber="103" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,1695,2009]" lastBlockId="3.[151,1436,151,320]" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="104" pageId="2" pageNumber="103">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,399,1695,1720]" pageId="2" pageNumber="103">Taxonomic remarks.</emphasis>
This species is listed as synonymous to 
<taxonomicName box="[868,1223,1695,1720]" class="Rhabditophora" family="Pseudocerotidae" genus="Pseudobiceros" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polycladida" pageId="2" pageNumber="103" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="species" species="flavomarginatus">
<emphasis box="[868,1223,1695,1720]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="103">Pseudobiceros flavomarginatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Faubel" box="[1269,1432,1695,1720]" pageId="2" pageNumber="116" refString="Faubel, A. (1984) The Polycladida, Turbellaria Proposal and establishment of a new system Part II. The Cotylea. Mitteilungen Hamburbischen Zoologischen Museum und Institute, 81, 189 - 259." type="journal article" year="1984">
Faubel (
<number box="[1362,1423,1696,1720]" pageId="2" pageNumber="103" value="1984.0">1984</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
. However, the original description (
<bibRefCitation author="Laidlaw" box="[552,712,1732,1757]" pageId="2" pageNumber="116" refString="Laidlaw, F. F. (1902) The marine Turbellaria, with an account of the anatomy of some of the species. The Fauna and Geography of the Maldive and Laccadive Archipelagoes, 1 (3), 282 - 312." type="journal article" year="1902">
Laidlaw 
<number box="[655,712,1732,1756]" pageId="2" pageNumber="103" value="1902.0">1902</number>
</bibRefCitation>
) divides 
<taxonomicName box="[821,963,1732,1757]" class="Rhabditophora" family="Pseudoceritidae" genus="Pseudoceros" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polycladida" pageId="2" pageNumber="103" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[821,963,1732,1757]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="103">Pseudoceros</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species in forms with a pair of penes or single penis, and 
<taxonomicName box="[351,564,1767,1792]" class="Rhabditophora" family="Pseudocerotidae" genus="Pseudobiceros" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polycladida" pageId="2" pageNumber="103" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="species" species="flavomarginatus">
<emphasis box="[351,564,1767,1792]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="103">P. flavomarginatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is under the species with single penis. This fact was already pointed out by 
<bibRefCitation author="Marcus" box="[151,321,1804,1829]" pageId="2" pageNumber="117" refString="Marcus, E. (1950) Turbellaria brasileiros (8). Boletim da Faculdade de Filosofia, Ciencias e Letras da Universidade de Sao Paulo, Zoologia, 15, 69 - 190." type="journal article" year="1950">
Marcus (
<number box="[253,313,1804,1829]" pageId="2" pageNumber="103" value="1950.0">1950</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, who considered 
<taxonomicName box="[524,858,1804,1829]" class="Rhabditophora" family="Pseudoceritidae" genus="Pseudoceros" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polycladida" pageId="2" pageNumber="103" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="species" species="flavomarginatus">
<emphasis box="[524,858,1804,1829]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="103">Pseudoceros flavomarginatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[918,1101,1804,1829]" class="Rhabditophora" family="Pseudocerotidae" genus="Pseudobiceros" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polycladida" pageId="2" pageNumber="103" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="species" species="luteomarginatus">
<emphasis box="[918,1101,1804,1829]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="103">luteomarginatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as separate species based on the number of gonopores and color information. The original 
<taxonomicName box="[868,1203,1839,1864]" class="Rhabditophora" family="Pseudoceritidae" genus="Pseudoceros" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polycladida" pageId="2" pageNumber="103" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="species" species="luteomarginatus">
<emphasis box="[868,1203,1839,1864]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="103">Pseudoceros luteomarginatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
description (
<bibRefCitation author="Yeri" pageId="2" pageNumber="117" refString="Yeri, M. &amp; Kaburaki, T. (1918) Description of some Japanese Polyclad Turbellaria. Journal of the College of Science, Tokyo Imperial University, 39 (9), 1 - 54." type="journal article" year="1918">
Yeri &amp; Kaburaki 
<number box="[262,320,1876,1900]" pageId="2" pageNumber="103" value="1918.0">1918</number>
</bibRefCitation>
) stated clearly (p. 
<number box="[530,561,1876,1900]" pageId="2" pageNumber="103" value="38.0">38</number>
; plate I, fig. 
<number box="[705,719,1876,1901]" pageId="2" pageNumber="103" value="5.0">5</number>
) that this 
<taxonomicName box="[834,1017,1876,1901]" class="Rhabditophora" family="Pseudocerotidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polycladida" pageId="2" pageNumber="103" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="family">Pseudocerotidae</taxonomicName>
has two male gonopores and smooth dorsal surface. So we think that the synonym and new combination presented by 
<bibRefCitation author="Faubel" box="[1061,1219,1911,1936]" pageId="2" pageNumber="116" refString="Faubel, A. (1984) The Polycladida, Turbellaria Proposal and establishment of a new system Part II. The Cotylea. Mitteilungen Hamburbischen Zoologischen Museum und Institute, 81, 189 - 259." type="journal article" year="1984">
Faubel (
<number box="[1153,1212,1912,1936]" pageId="2" pageNumber="103" value="1984.0">1984</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
was result of some confusion about the literature consulted. Thus we argue that 
<taxonomicName box="[871,1228,1948,1973]" class="Rhabditophora" family="Pseudocerotidae" genus="Pseudobiceros" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polycladida" pageId="2" pageNumber="103" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="species" species="flavomarginatus">
<emphasis box="[871,1228,1948,1973]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="103">Pseudobiceros flavomarginatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
should be left in 
<taxonomicName box="[151,293,1984,2009]" class="Rhabditophora" family="Pseudoceritidae" genus="Pseudoceros" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polycladida" pageId="2" pageNumber="103" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,293,1984,2009]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="103">Pseudoceros</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, as it has only one male gonopore, and that 
<taxonomicName box="[817,1151,1984,2009]" class="Rhabditophora" family="Pseudoceritidae" genus="Pseudoceros" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polycladida" pageId="2" pageNumber="103" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="species" species="luteomarginatus">
<emphasis box="[817,1151,1984,2009]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="103">Pseudoceros luteomarginatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
should be transferred to 
<taxonomicName box="[151,315,151,176]" class="Rhabditophora" family="Pseudocerotidae" genus="Pseudobiceros" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polycladida" pageId="3" pageNumber="104" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,315,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="104">Pseudobiceros</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, as it has two male gonopores. Since the transference of 
<taxonomicName box="[960,1171,151,176]" class="Rhabditophora" family="Pseudoceritidae" genus="Pseudoceros" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polycladida" pageId="3" pageNumber="104" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="species" species="luteomarginatus">
<emphasis box="[960,1171,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="104">P. luteomarginatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was indirectly done by 
<bibRefCitation author="Faubel" box="[151,312,188,213]" pageId="3" pageNumber="116" refString="Faubel, A. (1984) The Polycladida, Turbellaria Proposal and establishment of a new system Part II. The Cotylea. Mitteilungen Hamburbischen Zoologischen Museum und Institute, 81, 189 - 259." type="journal article" year="1984">
Faubel (
<number box="[244,305,188,212]" pageId="3" pageNumber="104" value="1984.0">1984</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, we consider that he had established this new combination. It is, however, unclear why the species mentioned above were ignored from Newman &amp; Cannon’s (
<number box="[836,966,224,248]" pageId="3" pageNumber="104" value="1994.1997">1994, 1997</number>
) 
<taxonomicName box="[982,1146,223,248]" class="Rhabditophora" family="Pseudocerotidae" genus="Pseudobiceros" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polycladida" pageId="3" pageNumber="104" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[982,1146,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="104">Pseudobiceros</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species list. 
<taxonomicName class="Rhabditophora" family="Pseudoceritidae" genus="Pseudoceros" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polycladida" pageId="3" pageNumber="104" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="species" species="flavomarginatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="104">Pseudoceros flavomarginatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was mentioned in the discussion of 
<taxonomicName authority="Newman &amp; Cannon 1994" authorityName="Newman &amp; Cannon" authorityYear="1994" box="[744,1360,260,285]" class="Rhabditophora" family="Pseudocerotidae" genus="Pseudobiceros" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polycladida" pageId="3" pageNumber="104" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="species" species="periculosus">
<emphasis box="[744,1045,260,285]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="104">Pseudobiceros periculosus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Newman" box="[1060,1352,260,284]" pageId="3" pageNumber="117" refString="Newman, L. J. &amp; Cannon, L. R. G. (1994) Pseudoceros and Pseudobiceros (Platyhelminthes, Polycladida, Pseudocertotidae) from eastern Australia and Papua New Guinea. Memoirs of the Queensland Museum, 37 (1), 205 - 266." type="journal article" year="1994">
Newman &amp; Cannon 
<number box="[1294,1352,260,284]" pageId="3" pageNumber="104" value="1994.0">1994</number>
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
where it was wrongly stated that Laidlaw did not give any additional details about gonopores.
</paragraph>
